<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870803-0110 </DOCNO><HL> General DynamicsGets Navy ContractOf $154.1 Million</HL><DD> 08/03/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> LK MOT LTV ETN UTX BA CW RTN ITT GE ROK GM GDAEROSPACE (ARO)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   General Dynamics Corp. received a $154.1 million Navy contract for Phalanx shipboard air-defense gun systems.    Units of General Motors Corp. were issued contracts totaling $91.5 million for spare parts for aircraft radars for the Navy and TOW missile equipment and motor vehicle engines for the Army.    Rockwell International Corp. units won $80.4 million in contracts for B-1B aircraft support equipment and engineering services for the Air Force, fighter aircraft engineering services for the Navy and CH-47 helicopter improvements for the Army.    RCA Corp., a unit of General Electric Co., was issued a $63.1 million Navy contract for Aegis shipbuilding engineering services.    ITT Corp. got a $55.5 million Air Force contract for missile test-range services.    Raytheon Co. received contracts totaling $48.5 million for Hawk missile equipment for the Army and development of ballistic missile equipment for the Air Force.    Curtiss-Wright Corp. was awarded a $37.7 million Air Force contract for F-16 aircraft equipment.    ILC Dover Inc. received a $33.7 million Air Force contract for transportable protection systems.    Boeing Co. was issued Air Force contracts totaling $33.3 million for B-1B aircraft support equipment.    Charles Stark Draper Laboratory received a $25.9 million Army contract to develop an inertial measurement unit.    Eaton Corp. won a $23.9 million Air Force contract for B-1B aircraft engineering services.    Units of United Technologies Corp. received contracts totaling $18.2 million for A-6E aircraft equipment and J-52 engine equipment for the Navy and C-130 aircraft equipment for the Air Force.    Units of Motorola Inc. won Army contracts totaling $14.4 million for classified services and electronic equipment.    LTV Corp. received a $12.3 million Air Force contract for radar bomb scoring equipment.    Lockheed Corp. was awarded a $10.1 million Navy contract for ballistic missile engineering services. </TEXT></DOC>